 and timestamp for each recommendation the user interacts with","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure occurs when tracking system schema differs from test expectations (field names, types, timestamp format). Unit mock might use wrong event structure or omit required fields. The tracking system's storage and retrieval must be verified—field names or formats might differ from assumptions. Integration test with actual tracking system needed.","test_description":"Simulate a user clicking a recommendation, query the tracking system, and verify the recorded event contains the correct product ID, correct position in the original list (with correct indexing), and a valid timestamp within the correct time window.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"The response time for generating recommendations stays under 200ms for a catalog of 100,000 products","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Performance characteristics are completely invisible at Unit level. Real failure occurs when algorithm complexity doesn't scale (e.g., O(n²) with 100k products). Integration test with scaled database (100k+ rows) is minimum to expose algorithmic complexity. System test with production-like infrastructure (indexing, caching, network) might reveal additional issues, but Integration catches the fundamental algorithmic failure.","test_description":"Load product database with 100,000 items, execute recommendation requests for varied user profiles (new user, browsing history, purchase history), and measure E2E latency distribution. Assert that p99 latency stays under 200ms across multiple runs.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.4,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"When a recommended product is purchased by the user, the recommendation algorithm deprioritizes it in subsequent requests","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"State persistence across multiple requests cannot be tested at Unit level. Real failure occurs when purchase state doesn't propagate to ranking logic, or when ranking state isn't updated after a purchase. Unit mock can't verify that ranking correctly reflects purchase history across requests. Integration test needed to verify purchase state is persisted and correctly affects ranking on subsequent calls.","test_description":"Request recommendations for a user, identify the top-ranked product, simulate a purchase of that product, request recommendations again immediately, and verify that the purchased product ranks lower (or is absent) in the new results.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":10,"description":"The recommendation results are deterministic for the same user state — requesting recommendations twice with no intervening user activity returns the same ranked list","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Non-determinism can arise from unordered data structures (hash iteration), concurrent updates, or floating-point precision—all invisible in Unit tests with mocked data. Real failure occurs when ordering differs between identical requests due to database state or concurrent access. Unit mock won't expose these issues. Integration test against real database with potential concurrent access needed to catch non-determinism.","test_description":"Request recommendations twice in rapid succession with no intervening user activity (no clicks, no purchases, no time passage), retrieve both result sets, and verify they are byte-identical (same products in same order).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":136